The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 26 August is 66,133 (7,622.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 21 August, there were 2,717 new confirmed cases (313.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 August, there were 2,474 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 10% (243 extra cases).
